					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5229475#post-3708422</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5229475/scp-3898#post-3708422</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 12 Feb 2018 21:44:13 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Genshed</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2643500</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>There are three kinds of SCPs, generally speaking, in which I have no idea what is going on.</p> <p>First, the badly written. Nobody really knows, except possibly the writer.</p> <p>Second, the well written but oblique in a way that challenges me. The Foundation knows, but I don't unless there's a hint in the comments.</p> <p>Last, the well written but cryptic in a way that challenges all observers. The Foundation is trying hard, and so am I.</p> <p>I put this in the last category. There's enough to give an idea, but not enough to really know. And that's what makes this a good SCP.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
